<item>
            <title>[LU-20118] lfs hsm_set --dirty --archive_id 1 on not archived file returns 0 with mdt rejects the request</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-20118</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When we use the lfs hsm_set command to set the file&apos;s hsm state, for a file that has HS_NONE state, --dirty returns 22 (EINVAL). When using --dirty --archive_id 1, it retuns success, but the mdt side actually rejects the setting, instrumentation with trace shows mdt fails the op, but returns rc as 0. It should return EINVAL since mdt rejects the request.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following is the repro steps:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
echo &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;hello &quot;&lt;/span&gt; &amp;gt;&amp;gt; a.txt
sudo lfs path2fid a.txt
[0x200000401:0xc3ba:0x0]
sudo lfs hsm_state a.txt
a.txt: (0x00000000)
&#160;
sudo&#160; lfs hsm_set a.txt --dirty --archive-id 1
echo $?
0
&#160;
sudo lfs hsm_state a.txt
a.txt: (0x00000000)
sudo&#160; lfs hsm_set a.txt --dirty
Can&apos;t change hsm flags &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; a.txt: Invalid argument
echo $?
22
&#160;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Review code (lustre/mdt/mdt_hsm.c) shows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;int&lt;/span&gt; mdt_hsm_state_set(struct tgt_session_info *tsi)
&#160;......
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-comment&quot;&gt;/* Change archive_id &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; provided. */&lt;/span&gt;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (hss-&amp;gt;hss_valid &amp;amp; HSS_ARCHIVE_ID) {
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; struct ptlrpc_request *req = mdt_info_req(info);
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; struct obd_export *exp = req-&amp;gt;rq_export;
&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; (!(ma-&amp;gt;ma_hsm.mh_flags &amp;amp; HS_EXISTS)) {
  &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; CDEBUG(D_HSM, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;Could not set an archive number &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; &quot;&lt;/span&gt;
  &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;DFID &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; HSM EXISTS flag is not set.\n&quot;&lt;/span&gt;,
  &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160;PFID(&amp;amp;info-&amp;gt;mti_body-&amp;gt;mbo_fid1));
&#160; &#160; ====&amp;gt;&#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; GOTO(out_unlock, rc);
  &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; &#160; }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;rc was set to 0. As result, it will return the 0 to the client.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;mdt trace shows:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
00000004:20000000:9.0:1775875099.458814:0:7575:0:(mdt_hsm.c:395:mdt_hsm_state_set()) Could not set an archive number &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;for&lt;/span&gt; [0x200000401:0xc3ba:0x0]&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; HSM EXISTS flag is not set.
&#160;
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It should return EINVAL to client since mdt rejects the invalid setting.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
